.TH LPF-RULES 8 "June 2026" "lpf 0.1.0-dev" "lpf Manual"
.SH NAME
lpf\-rules \- show generated or installed backend rules
.SH SYNOPSIS
lpf rules show
.SH DESCRIPTION
Show generated or installed backend rules with source\-policy annotations.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\-\-installed
show installed backend state
.TP
\-\-planned
show generated planned state
.SH EXAMPLES
lpf rules show \-\-installed
.SH FILES
/etc/lpf.conf
/var/lib/lpf/history
/var/lib/lpf/rollback
.SH SAFETY NOTES
This command is read\-only.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success.
Non\-zero when validation, planning, or host operations fail.
.SH SEE ALSO
lpf\-diff(8), lpf\-plan(8)
